editorialSummary.text: Long-running chain serving signature breakfast items & a variety of coffee drinks.

originalText.text: I really like Dunkin they have stepped up their game with food and holiday drinks. My go-to food Cheddar bagel bread warm with butter is so gooey good. Loving the loaded tater tots you can't have everyday( excessively much) but delicious. The holiday drinks so good - I just don't like that the cups are same size for more money üò£ but really invigorating drinks to warm you in these upcoming cold months and then their classic drinks they will bring in spring/summer

originalText.text: No comment on the food itself but the service here has been pretty consistently terrible. I've had several interactions with staff where they were surprisingly rude for no reason. I think there is a language barrier, but I'll often ask questions (about what products they have, or whatever) and this guy will just laugh at me and repeat "I don't know" and when I ask him to find someone else I can talk to he'll keep laughing at me and repeat "I don't know." It's a very surreal and unpleasant experience.

originalText.text: It's fine. It's Dunkin.  Corporate has a new thing where they hide the drinks away when you do a mobile order, making it harder to get your drink. Sometimes takes a while to get anything. Nice people working there.

originalText.text: I‚Äôd give them zero stars if I could. It is ALWAYS something wrong in there. Having a mobile order set up here is a joke. Either they run out of stuff so you show up and can‚Äôt get what you ordered. But worse, they NEVER have your order ready. They have a newer guy who I don‚Äôt think speaks English who is always doing everything but making your order. One day he and the woman training him were too busy laughing and joking. So when I asked where my order was, they looked dumbfounded and the woman training him says, ‚Äúoh it‚Äôs coming ma‚Äôam‚Äù then tried to rush to make it. I said forget it because I ordered 10 minutes prior to coming so that all I‚Äôd have to do is grab and go, not wait until they finish playing around before starting my order. So I left and got my money back. I should have learned my lesson from the many other times that had happened. Damn near the same thing happened again today. The same guy was doing everything but making my order. So when I asked for it, he and another guy looked dumbfounded again as they rushed to make my order. The other guy kept asking me what I wanted on my breakfast sandwich. I said I wanted it plain and asked why didn‚Äôt they read the order. He just got frustrated and ignored me. When he handed me my bag, there were no napkins. So I asked for some and he snatched the napkins from the dispenser behind the counter, looked at me with this annoyed blank stare and threw the napkins in the bag with an attitude. So after all of that, I grab my sandwich to go because I had to rush for the subway. When I went to eat it, I noticed they gave me pork sausage when I asked for turkey sausage. I don‚Äôt eat pork so I had wind up throwing the meat away. So I wound up paying $6 for a croissant since that‚Äôs the only part of the sandwich I could eat. The people here are incompetent and easily distracted and I will NEVER go back!!! EVER!!!

originalText.text: Very rude customer service man at the register was yelling got my order wrong and then wanted me to pay for an item I did not order. I spoke to another staff person and was ignored. After over 10 years of going here and last week I brought a friend here and she spent a great deal of money. Do not go to this location the Starbucks a block away has much better customer service and much better coffee.
